Korean Style Cheesey Corn Dog 🧀🌭

🧀 Mozzarella cheese (cut in thick strips)
🍢 Wooden skewers
🌾 Yeast
🍬 Sugar
💧 Warm water
🌾 Maida (all-purpose flour)
🧂 Salt
🍞 Panko breadcrumbs
🛢️ Oil for frying
🌶️ Sriracha mayo (for serving)
🍅 Ketchup (for serving)

Method:
1️⃣ Mozzarella cheese ko thick strips mai cut karke skewers mai insert karo
2️⃣ Coating banane ke liye yeast sugar aur warm water ko mix karke activate hone do
3️⃣ Ab maida aur salt add karke dough ready karo
4️⃣ Dough ko 10-15 min ke liye rakh do jab tak size double na ho jaaye
5️⃣ Ab cheese sticks ko dough se coat karo aur panko breadcrumbs mai roll karo
6️⃣ Inhe golden crispy hone tak fry karo
7️⃣ Serve karo sriracha mayo aur ketchup ke saath

#KoreanCornDog #CheesySnack #StreetFoodStyle #FoodieFemmePooja #MozzarellaLover #CornDogRecipe #CheesePull

Street Style Chinese Bhel with Leftover Roti

📝 Ingredients:
🫓 Leftover roti (cut into small pieces)
🛢️ Oil (for frying)
🧅 Onion (sliced)
🥬 Cabbage (shredded)
🫑 Capsicum (sliced)
🥕 Carrot (julienned)
🧄 Ginger garlic paste
🌶️ Green chili (chopped)
🥣 Soya sauce
🌶️ Schezwan chutney
🧂 Salt
⚫ Black pepper powder

👩‍🍳 Method:
1️⃣ Cut leftover roti into small pieces and shallow fry in hot oil until crispy
2️⃣ In a separate pan sauté onions, cabbage, capsicum, and carrots
3️⃣ Add ginger garlic paste and green chili, mix well
4️⃣ Add soya sauce, schezwan chutney, salt, and black pepper, mix everything
5️⃣ Toss in crispy roti pieces and quickly mix
6️⃣ Serve hot and enjoy the fusion twist

#ChineseBhel #LeftoverRotiRecipe #StreetStyleSnacks #HealthySnacking #EasyRecipes #DesiTwist #TastyAndHealthy

Homemade Soft Tofu 
🫘 Ingredients
Soya beans – 1 cup
Water – as required
Vinegar – 2 to 3 tbsp

👩‍🍳 Method
🛏️ Overnight soak soya beans in water
🤲 Remove the peel from soaked beans
🧊 Add water and blend in mixing jar to make a smooth mixture
🧺 Transfer to a muslin cloth and squeeze out the soya milk
🔁 Repeat blending and straining 2 to 3 times for more milk
🔥 Heat the extracted soya milk
🧴 Add vinegar to the hot milk and let it curdle
🧊 Transfer curdled mixture to muslin cloth and press it into shape
❄️ Refrigerate for 3 to 4 days for use

#HomemadeTofu #VeganProtein #HealthyTofu #TofuRecipe #PlantBasedCooking #EasyTofu #SoyaMilk #DairyFree

Crispy Potato Wedges 
🥔 Ingredients
Aloo – 3 to 4 medium size
Oil – 2 tbsp + for frying
Corn flour – 2 to 3 tbsp
Salt – as per taste
Black pepper powder – 1 tsp
Oregano – 1 tsp
Chili flakes – 1 tsp

👩‍🍳 Method
🔪 Cut unpeeled potatoes into wedges
🥣 Add them to a bowl with oil corn flour salt black pepper powder oregano and chili flakes
🤲 Mix everything well to coat the wedges evenly
🔥 Fry in medium hot oil until crispy and golden brown
🍽️ Serve hot with your favourite dip

#CrispyWedges #PotatoSnacks #EasySnacks #QuickRecipe #AlooLovers #HomeMadeSnacks #FriedGoodness #CrunchyBites

Aam Papad 

🛒 Ingredients:
🥭 Kachha Aam (Raw Mango)
🍯 Gud Powder (Jaggery Powder)
🧂 Namak (Salt)
🖤 Kala Namak (Black Salt)
🌶️ Red Chilli Flakes
🛢️ Tel (Oil – for greasing)

👩‍🍳 Method:
1️⃣ Kachha aam ko chhote tukdon mein cut karo
2️⃣ Pressure cooker mein 2–3 seeti tak paka lo
3️⃣ Thoda thanda hone ke baad aam ko ache se mash karo
4️⃣ Ab usmein daalo gud powder, namak, kala namak aur red chilli flakes
5️⃣ Sab kuch ache se mix karo jab tak ek smooth aur transparent mixture ban jaaye
6️⃣ Ek plate lo, usmein halka sa tel brush karo
7️⃣ Aam papad ka mixture usmein spread karo
8️⃣ Ab ise 2 din dhoop mein sukhne do
9️⃣ Jab sukh jaaye to plate se nikaal lo — ready hai hamara homemade Aam Papad

Surti Style Cheese Paneer Ghotala

This creamy cheesy spicy and rich paneer dish is an iconic street food of Surat Packed with veggies butter and overflowing cheese this dish will make you crave more with every bite Let’s get into the full recipe so you can recreate this magic at home

🧾 Ingredients

Veggies & Base
• 🧈 2 tbsp Butter
• 🛢️ 1 tbsp Oil
• 🌶️ 2 tsp Green chili paste
• 🧄 2 tsp Ginger garlic paste
• 🧅 2 medium Onions finely chopped
• 🍅 2 medium Tomatoes finely chopped
• 🫑 1 Capsicum finely chopped
• 🥬 1 cup Spinach boiled and mashed

Spices
• 🧂 Salt as per taste
• 🧂 1 5 tsp Pav Bhaji Masala
• 🧂 ½ tsp Cumin Powder
• 🧂 ½ tsp Coriander Powder

Special Flavors
• 🧄🌿 1 tbsp Fresh green garlic chopped
• 🌿 2 tbsp Fresh coriander finely chopped

Dairy & Creaminess
• 🧀 1 5 cups Grated Paneer
• 🧀 1 cup Grated Processed Cheese like Amul or any melting cheese
• 🥛 ¼ cup Fresh Cream
• 🥛 ¼ cup Milk optional to adjust thickness

⸻

🍳 Method

1 🔪 Prep First
• Grate the paneer and cheese
• Chop all veggies finely
• Boil spinach cool it and mash well

2 🔥 Start Cooking
• Heat butter and oil in a broad pan or tawa
• Add cumin optional then ginger garlic paste and green chili paste sauté for a minute

3 🧅 Add Veggies
• Add chopped onions and cook till golden
• Add tomatoes and capsicum sauté till tomatoes turn soft
• Mash this mixture lightly using a pav bhaji masher

4 🥬 Mix in Spinach
• Add mashed spinach and mix everything well
• Let it cook for 2–3 minutes till everything blends nicely

5 🧂 Time for Spices
• Add salt pav bhaji masala cumin and coriander powder
• Add green garlic and coriander leaves
• Mix and mash again add a bit more butter if needed

6 🧀 Cheesy Goodness
• Add grated paneer mix well
• Add grated cheese and fresh cream let it melt and get creamy
• If mixture becomes too thick pour a little milk and stir to balance

7 🍽️ Serve Hot
• Serve piping hot with buttered pav naan or paratha
• Garnish with more cheese and coriander if desired 

#CheesePaneerGotala #SurtiStreetFood #PaneerLoversDelight #DesiCheeseFix #IndianStreetStyle #TryThisRecipe

Tandoori Corn Tikka

🌽 Ingredients
🌽 Sweet corn (bite-sized pieces)
🧂 Salt
🧄 Ginger-garlic paste
🧈 Mustard oil
🟡 Haldi (turmeric powder)
🌿 Dhaniya powder (coriander)
🌰 Jeera powder (cumin)
🌶️ Red chili powder
🧂 Garam masala
🌿 Kasuri methi
🍋 Lemon juice
🧈 Besan (gram flour)
🥣 Dahi (curd)

🔥 Method
	1.	Sweet corn ko bite-sized pieces mai cut karke 10-15 min steam karein aur cool hone dein
	2.	Ek bowl mai dahi, ginger-garlic paste, mustard oil, haldi, dhaniya-jeera powder, red chili powder, garam masala, salt, kasuri methi, besan aur lemon juice add karke ache se mix karein
	3.	Is marinade mai corn ko mila kar 10 min ke liye chhod dein
	4.	Ab corn pieces ko skewers mai laga kar gas flame ya oven pe tandoor karein jab tak thoda char ho jaye
	5.	Upar se thoda lemon juice daalein aur serve karein

#TandooriCornTikka #VegTikka #CornRecipes #IndianSnacks #TandooriLove #HomemadeTikka

Dryfruit Kachori 
(10 to 15 kachori)

🌶️ Ingredients for Masala Stuffing
🌿 Laung (cloves) - 2 piece
🌿 Kali mirch (peppercorn) 4 to 5
🌿 Tejpatta 1
🌿 Saunf 1 tbsp
🌿 Dhania seeds 1 tbsp 
🌿 Jeera 1 tbsp
🍘 Moong dal namkeen 100 gm (1 cup)
🧂 Namak 1 tsp
🌶️ Lal mirch powder 1 tbsp
🌶️ Garam masala 1 tsp
🍬 Cheeni 3 tbsp
🍋 Imli ka pulp 2 tbsp
🌰 Safed til 1 tbsp
🥜 Mix dryfruits (badam, kaju, kishmish etc) 1 cup
🛢️ Tel (for binding) 2 tbsp

🌾 Ingredients for Outer Layer
🌾 Maida 2 cup
🧂 Namak 1 tsp
🌿 Ajwain 1 tsp
🧈 Ghee 3 tbsp
💧 Pani (for kneading and sealing) 1 cup

👩‍🍳 Method
1️⃣ Ek pan me laung, peppercorn, tejpatta, saunf, dhaniya aur jeera ko dry roast karo
2️⃣ Inhe mixer jar me daal ke moong dal namkeen, namak, lal mirch powder, garam masala aur cheeni ke saath grind karke powder bana lo
3️⃣ Is powder me imli ka pulp, safed til aur mix dryfruits daalo
4️⃣ Thoda sa oil daal kar is masale ki achhi binding kar lo
5️⃣ Ab stuffing ke chhote balls bana lo
6️⃣ Maida me namak, ajwain aur ghee daal ke medium soft dough bana lo
7️⃣ Dough ko rest dekar haathon se flatten karo
8️⃣ Beech me stuffing daal kar corner me paani lagao aur seal kar ke kachori shape do
9️⃣ Low to medium flame pe kachori ko golden crispy hone tak fry karo
🔟 Serve garma garam

#dryfruitkachori #kachorilovers #festivesnack #indiansnack #homemadewithlove #stuffedkachori #kachorirecipe #snacktime

3-Ingredient No-Bake Chocolate Cake

🍪 Ingredients
🍘 Krackjack biscuits (72 pieces)
🍫 Dark or milk chocolate (400gm)
🥣 Fresh cream 1 cup 
🍫 White melted chocolate (for garnish, optional)

👩‍🍳 Method
1️⃣ Krackjack biscuits ko ready rakho
2️⃣ Chocolate ko melt karo aur usme fresh cream add karo
3️⃣ Achhe se mix karo jab tak glossy mixture ban jaye
4️⃣ Biscuit ke upar chocolate mixture spread karo aur aise layers banao
5️⃣ Uneven biscuits ko layers me rakhte jao
6️⃣ Do layers banane ke baad poori cake ko chocolate se cover karo
7️⃣ Upar se white melted chocolate se decorate karo ya apni pasand ka garnish karo
8️⃣ Cake ko fridge me 30 minutes ke liye set hone do
9️⃣ Set hone ke baad slice karo aur enjoy karo

#3ingredientcake #nobakecake #instantcake #chocolatecake #easycakerecipe #homemadedessert #cookwithlove #quickdessert

Crispy Paneer in Spicy Korean Sauce

🌶️🧀🍅🥢

Ingredients:
🧀 Paneer – 250 gm (cut into finger size)
🌽 Cornflour – 2 tbsp
🧂 Salt – to taste
🧈 Black pepper – ½ tsp
🌿 Oil – for frying

For Korean Sauce:
🧄 Garlic – 1 tbsp (finely chopped)
🫚 Ginger – 1 tsp (finely chopped)
🌶️ Gochujang – 2 tbsp
🍜 Soya sauce – 1 tbsp
🍅 Tomato ketchup – 2 tbsp
🍯 Brown sugar – 1 tbsp
🍋 Lemon juice – 1 tsp
💧 Water – ¼ cup
🌽 Cornflour slurry – 1 tbsp cornflour + 2 tbsp water
🌿 Sesame seeds – 1 tsp
🌿 Spring onion – 2 tbsp

Method:
Paneer ko cornflour, salt aur pepper ke saath mix karo, phir golden aur crispy hone tak fry karo
Ek pan mein oil garam karo, usme garlic aur ginger daal kar thoda sauté karo
Gochujang, soya sauce, ketchup, brown sugar, aur lemon juice daal kar mix karo
Pani aur cornflour slurry daal ke sauce ko thick hone tak cook karo
Fried paneer ko sauce mein daal kar ache se coat karo
Sesame seeds aur spring onions daal kar serve karo

#CrispyPaneer #KoreanSaucePaneer #PaneerLover #FusionFood #SpicyTreat #PaneerSnack #FoodieFun #DesiTwist
